<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>shoot a goal • shoot at the goal</xh5><p> <i>shoot a goal</i>—(Sport) score a goal: The ball had come in from the right, and McLuckie killed it, and <u>shot a goal</u>.</p><p> <i>shoot at the goal—</i>1. <i>(Sport)</i> kick the ball, etc. in an attempt to score a goal: In the last hockey game, Mike Modano <u>shot at the goal</u> several times. 2. have smth. in mind as an object; strive for smth.: When it is achieved there will be other <u>goals for them to shoot at</u>.</p> </entry>
